Since $H$ lies on line $BE,$ $\overrightarrow{BH}$ is a scalar multiple of $\overrightarrow{BE}.$  Let $\overrightarrow{BH} = k \overrightarrow{BE}.$  Then
\[9 \overrightarrow{AB} + 13k \overrightarrow{BE} + 7 \overrightarrow{AC} = \mathbf{0}.\]Since $\overrightarrow{AB},$ $\overrightarrow{BE},$ and $\overrightarrow{AC}$ are not collinear, $9 + 13k + 7 = 0,$ so $k = -\frac{16}{13}.$

